.TH "radeon_fence_wait_any" 9 "radeon_fence_wait_any" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
radeon_fence_wait_any \- wait for a fence to signal on any ring
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" radeon_fence_wait_any
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ","
.BI "struct radeon_fence **fences "  ","
.BI "bool intr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon device pointer
.IP "fences" 12
radeon fence object(s)
.IP "intr" 12
use interruptable sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for any requested fence to signal (all asics).  Fence
array is indexed by ring id.  \fIintr\fP selects whether to use
interruptable (true) or non-interruptable (false) sleep when
waiting for the fences. Used by the suballocator.
Returns 0 if any fence has passed, error for all other cases.
